@SteveDiamond @akshayka this is the main technical point we need to address. When the web docs compile they record the version of the current cvxpy installation. That version is displayed as the header of the browser window that displays cvxpy.org. Right now it's "Welcome to CVXPY 1.1 -- CVXPY 1.1.17 documentation" (since gh-pages haven't been rebuilt when 1.1.18 was released).

If we're going to support multiple versions of cvxpy simultaneously then we either need to host separate documentation for each supported minor release, or we need the web docs to not auto-populate the version number based on the current installation. I think that most projects take the first approach, but I don't know how to go about doing that.

A relevant detail: the version number of a cvxpy installation contains git commit information unless setup.py indicates we're on a release branch. Master will not be a release branch moving forward. So when I build the web docs on this branch, the in-browser header for cvxpy.org says "Welcome to CVXPY -- CVXPY 1.2.0dev0+1074.514cead documentation".

