I think calling `Set()` with rvalue reference being itself is not technically incorrect use. So I am not sure if we want to restrict its use and `OT_ASSERT()` on it.

It can happen in a statement equivalent to ```name.Set(static_cast<HeapString &&>(name))```.

Though I agree that it is very unlikely to see such a statement (directly as is) used in the code, I think a very similar/equivalent statement can happen indirectly through using a return value from a function/method, compiler inlining the function/method along with RVO (return value optimization), and use of `std::move` (which behaves practically as a `static_cast<HeapString &&>()`). 

Here is a somewhat contrived example to create such a situation but I think similar pattern may happen in the code as well:
```
struct SomeType 
{
   HeapString mName;
   HeapString mOtherName;

   HeapString GetName(void) { return std::move(mName); }
   HeapString GetOtherName(void) { return std::move(mOtherName); }

   void SomeMethod(void)
   {
        bool useOtherName = false;
 
        // Later in code somewhere 
        mName.Set(useOtherName ? GetOtherName() : GetName()));

```

